    "id": "kp-3.7-01",
    "section": "3.7",
    "order": 1,
    "title": "Perpendicular Lines",
    "title_zh": "垂直线",
    "explanation": {
      "en": "**Perpendicular lines** are lines that intersect at a right angle ($90^\\circ$).\n\n**Gradients** of perpendicular lines have a product of $-1$. If line $L_1$ has gradient $m_1$ and $L_2$ has gradient $m_2$, then $L_1 \\perp L_2$ means:\n$$m_1 \\times m_2 = -1 \\quad \\text{or} \\quad m_2 = -\\frac{1}{m_1}$$\n\nThis is called the **negative reciprocal**. For example, if a line has gradient $3$, the perpendicular line has gradient $-\\frac{1}{3}$.",
      "zh": "**垂直线**是以直角 ($90^\\circ$) 相交的直线。\n\n垂直线的**斜率乘积**为 $-1$。如果直线 $L_1$ 的斜率为 $m_1$，直线 $L_2$ 的斜率为 $m_2$，那么 $L_1 \\perp L_2$ 意味着：\n$$m_1 \\times m_2 = -1 \\quad \\text{或} \\quad m_2 = -\\frac{1}{m_1}$$\n\n这被称为**负倒数**。例如，如果一条直线的斜率是 $3$，那么垂直它的直线斜率就是 $-\\frac{1}{3}$。"
    },
